This is an interesting topic but there's one piece missing from this subject. It's not about all or nothing, to help or not to help, it's about finding moderation. Help locally and when you can, it will give you a sense of happiness nothing else can and you will be blessed for it. However, you do not need to answer the call to serve every time there is a need. There will always be a need, somewhere, for someone, and someday that someone might just be you. So help, but allow others to help you too. Find happiness in all that you do, when your in the service of others, and when you're in the service of yourself. Remember, everything in moderation and find a balance.
